cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.NA. 

The paper deals with a machine learning problem involving binary matrix completion, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and recommender systems (cs.IR). The use of nonconvex regularizers is a novel approach that has shown better empirical performance in standard matrix completion (cs.LG). The paper also provides a recovery guarantee for the proposed model, which involves optimization techniques (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the experiments conducted on synthetic and real-world data sets involve numerical analysis (cs.NA).
